Subject: Attention Traversal Policy Source

Description: Raw preserved source for policy governing correlation, cross-reference, folding, unwinding, and deeper probing around a focal point.

& [DictatedAttentionTraversalPolicySource] is the preserved user source for attention traversal
  @ [user_statement] "now can you write a policy about how to attend attention to correlate and cross-reference and fold and unwind and all manner of reaching into and through from one subject to another"
  @ [user_statement] "following that focal point, and draw into it the periphery realizations and relate them together as the framework for how to triangulate around subjects for probing deeper thinking"

  + [focal_point] is the active attention direction that traversal must follow
  + [correlate] is finding weighted relation between subject surfaces
  + [cross_reference] is citing and linking exterior SOP, scan, tracker, narrative, or graph records without absorbing them
  + [fold] is composing periphery realization, relation, evidence, and focal subject into a bounded candidate
  + [unwind] is decomposing the candidate back into source anchors, relations, uncertainty, and outside
  + [reach_through] is moving from one subject to another through an explicit typed relation
  + [triangulation] is probing a subject with several distinct anchors plus an outside boundary
  + [deeper_thinking] is the controlled deepening of a focal subject through repeated fold and unwind passes

  = must: begin from the focal point
  = must: draw periphery into focus only through explicit relation, liminal draw, or policy-governed traversal
  = must: triangulate before deepening
  = must: preserve source anchors and outside
  - never: wander through correlations without returning to focal point
